DEPRESSOMETER METHOD
All clients and therapists signed an informed consent form, indicating that they
agreed to participate in the study. Clients received the treatment free of charge. All
sessions were recorded using six high-resolution microphones (which were scattered
around the two armchairs), and videotaped by three high-resolution cameras (one
focused on the client, the other on the therapist and the third on both to assess their
interaction). Both clients and therapists filled out pre- and post-session self-report
questionnaires (session by session). Besides, at the end of treatment, clients were
invited to a post-treatment assessment meeting (55 clients showed) and a three-month
follow-up meeting (49 clients showed), in which the HRSD and MINI interviews were
administered again. Overall, self-report questionnaires were filled out by the clients at
the three assessment periods; i.e., pre-treatment, post-treatment, and follow-up.
Treatment Clinical Change Indices
Among patients who began treatment above the clinical cutoff, change indices were
examined separately for each measure. For the HRSD, among the 51 patients who
began at or above the HRSD clinical cutoff (14), 35 patients (68.6%) ended treatment
below it. For the BDI, among the 43 patients who began at or above the BDI clinical
